IDENTIFICATION: We consulted descriptions and measurements of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D1BFF97FF9FE8E01698FBD054A6" baseAuthorityName="Spix" baseAuthorityYear="1823" box="[909,1114,646,670]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="planirostris">
<emphasis id="B90EEA8AFF97FF9FE8E01698FBD054A6" box="[909,1114,646,670]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">Artibeus planirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FF97FF9FE9A216B7FCE254F8" author="Husson, A. M." box="[719,872,680,704]" pageId="23" pageNumber="23" pagination="1 - 282" refId="ref37541" refString="Husson, A. M. 1962. The bats of Suriname. Zoologische Verhandelingen (Rijksmuseum van Natuurlijke Historie, Leiden) 58: 1 - 282." type="journal article" year="1962">Husson (1962</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FF97FF9FE81816B7FC2154F9" author="Husson, A. M." box="[885,939,681,705]" pageId="23" pageNumber="23" refId="ref37570" refString="Husson, A. M. 1978. The mammals of Suriname. Zoologische Monographieen van het Rijksmuseum van Natuurlijke Historie (Leiden) 2: 569 pp. + 151 pls." type="book" year="1978">1978</bibRefCitation>
), 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FF97FF9FE8AC16B7FBDE54F9" author="Patten, D. R." box="[961,1108,681,705]" pageId="23" pageNumber="23" refId="ref40939" refString="Patten, D. R. 1971. A review of the large species of Artibeus (Chiroptera: Phyllostomidae) from western South America, Ph. D. dissertation, Texas A &amp; M University, College Station, 194 pp." type="book" year="1971">Patten (1971)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FF97FF9FEF0F16B6FD7A54DB" author="Handley, C. O., Jr." pageId="23" pageNumber="23" pagination="163 - 172" refId="ref36981" refString="Handley, C. O., Jr. 1987. New species of mammals from northern South America: fruit-eating bats, genus Artibeus Leach. Fieldiana Zoology, New Series 39: 163 - 172." type="book chapter" year="1987">Handley (1987)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FF97FF9FE99416D5FB0354DB" author="Brosset, A. &amp; P. Charles-Dominique" box="[761,1161,715,739]" pageId="23" pageNumber="23" pagination="509 - 560" refId="ref33466" refString="Brosset, A., and P. Charles-Dominique. 1990. The bats from French Guiana: a taxonomic, faunistic and ecological approach. Mammalia 54: 509 - 560." type="journal article" year="1990">Brosset and Charles-Dominique (1990)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FF97FF9FEFFF16D5FCF8553D" author="Lim, B. K. &amp; D. E. Wilson" pageId="23" pageNumber="23" pagination="763 - 768" refId="ref38453" refString="Lim, B. K., and D. E. Wilson. 1993. Taxonomic status of Artibeus amplus (Chiroptera: Phyllostomidae) in northern South America. Journal of Mammalogy 74: 763 - 768." type="journal article" year="1993">Lim and Wilson (1993)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FF97FF9FE81016F3FC79553D" author="Lim, B. K." box="[893,1011,749,773]" pageId="23" pageNumber="23" pagination="65 - 71" refId="ref38414" refString="Lim, B. K. 1997. Morphometric differentiation and species status of the allopatric fruit-eating bats Artibeus jamaicensis and A. planirostris in Venezuela. Studies on Neotropical Fauna and Environment 32: 65 - 71." type="journal article" year="1997">Lim (1997)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FF97FF9FE89216F3FB02553D" author="Hollis, L." box="[1023,1160,749,773]" pageId="23" pageNumber="23" pagination="1 - 6" refId="ref37294" refString="Hollis, L. 2005. Artibeus planirostris. Mammalian Species 775: 1 - 6." type="journal article" year="2005">Hollis (2005)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FF97FF9FE9C31711FCDC551F" author="Lim, B. K." box="[686,854,783,807]" pageId="23" pageNumber="23" pagination="225 - 274" refId="ref38551" refString="Lim, B. K., et al. 2005. Results of the ALCOA Foundation-Suriname expeditions. XIV. Mammals of Brownsberg Nature Park, Suriname. Annals of Carnegie Museum 74: 225 - 274." type="journal article" year="2005">Lim et al. (2005)</bibRefCitation>
. Currently three subspecies are recognized: 
<emphasis id="B90EEA8AFF97FF9FE867172CFCF75572" box="[778,893,818,842]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">A. p. fallax</emphasis>
(
<collectingCountry id="F36D7608FF97FF9FE8E6172CFC725572" box="[907,1016,818,842]" name="Venezuela" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
[south and east of the Orinoco river]), 
<collectingCountry id="F36D7608FF97FF9FE8E2174AFC645554" box="[911,1006,852,876]" name="Trinidad and Tobago" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">Trinidad</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F36D7608FF97FF9FE891174AFBD35554" box="[1020,1113,852,876]" name="Grenada" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">Grenada</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F36D7608FF97FF9FEF0A174AFB315554" box="[1127,1211,852,876]" name="Guyana" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">Guyana</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F36D7608FF97FF9FE9C11768FC8255B6" box="[684,776,886,910]" name="Suriname" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">Surinam</collectingCountry>
, French Guiana, and the lower Amazon basin of 
<collectingCountry id="F36D7608FF97FF9FE86F1787FCCB5589" box="[770,833,921,945]" name="Brazil" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">Brazil</collectingCountry>
), 
<emphasis id="B90EEA8AFF97FF9FE83D1787FC5C5589" box="[848,982,921,945]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">A. p. hercules</emphasis>
(southeastern 
<collectingCountry id="F36D7608FF97FF9FEF011787FD4155EB" name="Colombia" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">Colombia</collectingCountry>
and the eastern lowlands of 
<collectingCountry id="F36D7608FF97FF9FE89817A5FBC755EB" box="[1013,1101,955,979]" name="Ecuador" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F36D7608FF97FF9FEF3517A5FB0155EA" box="[1112,1163,955,978]" name="Peru" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">Peru</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="F36D7608FF97FF9FE9C017C3FD7055CD" box="[685,762,989,1013]" name="Bolivia" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
), and 
<emphasis id="B90EEA8AFF97FF9FE85217C3FC7855CD" box="[831,1010,989,1013]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">
A. p. 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D1BFF97FF9FE81317C3FC7855CD" baseAuthorityName="Spix" baseAuthorityYear="1823" box="[894,1010,989,1013]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="planirostris">planirostris</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
(southern 
<collectingCountry id="F36D7608FF97FF9FEF0317C3FB3355CD" box="[1134,1209,989,1013]" name="Bolivia" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, northern 
<collectingCountry id="F36D7608FF97FF9FE87A17E1FC0E522F" box="[791,900,1023,1047]" name="Argentina" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F36D7608FF97FF9FE8F9101EFC725220" box="[916,1016,1024,1048]" name="Paraguay" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
, and eastern and southern 
<collectingCountry id="F36D7608FF97FF9FE862103CFCC75202" box="[783,845,1058,1082]" name="Brazil" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">Brazil</collectingCountry>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FF97FF9FE80C103CFBDA5202" author="Marques-Aguiar, S. A." box="[865,1104,1058,1082]" pageId="23" pageNumber="23" pagination="301 - 321" refId="ref39372" refString="Marques-Aguiar, S. A. 2008 (&quot; 2007 &quot;). Genus Artibeus Leach, 1821. In A. L. Gardner (editor), Mammals of South America, vol. 1: Marsupials, xenarthrans, shrews, and bats: 301 - 321. Chicago: University of Chicago Press." type="book chapter" year="2008">Marques-Aguiar, 2008</bibRefCitation>
). The only major morphological difference recognized among subspecies is that 
<emphasis id="B90EEA8AFF97FF9FE8061079FC725246" box="[875,1016,1126,1150]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">A. p. hercules</emphasis>
tends to be larger than the other subspecies (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FF97FF9FE8AB1097FBC35299" author="Hollis, L." box="[966,1097,1161,1185]" pageId="23" pageNumber="23" pagination="1 - 6" refId="ref37294" refString="Hollis, L. 2005. Artibeus planirostris. Mammalian Species 775: 1 - 6." type="journal article" year="2005">Hollis, 2005</bibRefCitation>
). Based on distribution, the voucher material from Mayo River basin should correspond to the subspecies 
<emphasis id="B90EEA8AFF97FF9FEF3310D0FD565330" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">A. p. hercules</emphasis>
. However, measurements of our material span the published variation of size for the entire species, and hence do not conform to published characteristics of the subspecies. We therefore recommend against formally recognizing subspecies in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D1BFF97FF9FEF0A1167FC94538B" baseAuthorityName="Spix" baseAuthorityYear="1823" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="planirostris">
<emphasis id="B90EEA8AFF97FF9FEF0A1167FC94538B" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">Artibeus planirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
until truly diagnostic characters can be found, including additional data from molecular markers.
</paragraph>
